docs.abstract: Despite all the mortal threats it faces, this continent could yet represent a beacon of hope engendered by a spirit of collaboration.
docs.snippet: Despite all the mortal threats it faces, this continent could yet represent a beacon of hope engendered by a spirit of collaboration.
docs.lead_paragraph: Re “With deal, China eyes Antarctica” (News, April 24): Questions about China’s motives in expanding its Antarctic operations are paralleled by condemnation for its depletion of Africa’s resources and degradation of its environment. China’s development aid for Africa is motivated by a mixture of altruism, empathy, humanitarianism as well as economic and strategic gain. But in its sprint toward prosperity, China is seen as neglectful of its environmental obligations. As an emerging donor, it has yet to garner the humanitarian credibility that postwar reconstruction help for Germany and Japan fostered for the United States and Britain. It is no wonder that China remains a target of suspicion on the world stage.
